1 B. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
2 fund for the Oklahoma Department of Emergency Management to be
3 designated the “Canine Cooperative Grant Program Revolving Fund”.
4 The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year
5 limitations, and shall consist of all monies received from
6 legislative appropriations, private donations, and federal grant
7 programs. All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
8 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
9 Department of Emergency Management for the administration of the
10 Canine Cooperative Grant Program. Expenditures from the fund shall
11 be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
12 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
13 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
14 C. The Oklahoma Department of Emergency Management may retain
15 five percent (5%) of the proceeds of the fund annually to be used
16 for the administration of the program.
17 D. Subject to the availability of funds, the program shall have
18 the following annual limits for grants:
19 1. Grants not to exceed Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00) per
20 county sheriff for canine purchases or canine training;
21 2. Grants not to exceed Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00) per
22 municipal police department for canine purchases or canine training;
